div class="h-screen flex flex-col md:justify-center items-center"
  div class="flex flex-col items-center max-w-screen-md"
    div class="block md:w-64 w-48 mt-5 md:mt-0"
      a href="#{root_path}"
        = inline_svg "media/packs/app/logo.svg"
    div class="my-5 mb-10 w-10/12"
      div class="relative" data-controller="search"
        = form_tag search_url(version: ruby_version), method: :get, id: "search" do
          input class="bg-white shadow-md rounded px-3 py-3 w-full" data-target="search.input" name="q" type="text" autocapitalize="off" autocorrect="off" autocomplete="off" placeholder="Search Ruby Documentation" aria-label="Search" title="Search" autofocus="yes"
          button type="submit" name="submit" class="absolute right-0 inset-y-0 px-4"
            span class="fa fa-search"
    div class="xl:w-full px-5 py-3 bg-red-900 w-10/12 md:w-full text-white rounded"
      h2 class="md:text-3xl text-2xl"
        | Hello World!
      p
        | Thanks for checking out Ruby API. This project aims to make Ruby's documentation more easy to search and find what you're looking for. Much of the site is currently a work in progress so some search queries may return odd results, and things will probably change without warning. If you have any queries, questions, or bug reports feel free to reach Colby via:
      a href="https://github.com/colby-swandale/ruby-api"
        i class="fab fa-github"
        |  colby-swandale/ruby-api
      br
      a href="https://twitter.com/oceanicpanda"
        i class="fab fa-twitter"
        |  @oceanicpanda
